    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-06-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="300"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Dix</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 100.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">Paris,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-06-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 28, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to transmit herewith á
                    translation of a communication received from the Marquis de Moustier, minister
                    of foreign affairs, in relation to the appointment of Mr. Samuel B. Ruggles as a
                    delegate to the international conference now holding its sessions in Paris.</p>
                <p>I am, with great respect, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN A. DIX.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary
                            of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
